{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781683255,"nonce":"wwX4uc+ou/3NF9R6HISjIi/Fw9E=","title":"Add a SQLite backend","message":"There is no SQLite backend (only squealy-postgresql and squealy-mysql). A SQLite backend is high value for tests and small/embedded apps, and is a good forcing function for keeping backend-specific behavior behind the Backend trait rather than leaking pg-isms into core.\n\nScope: a squealy-sqlite crate implementing the Backend / Connection traits, SQL rendering, bind/decode, and introspection, mirroring the structure of squealy-postgresql. Map the logical column types (HasColumnType) to SQLite affinities and document where SQLite cannot honor a feature (e.g. certain constraint/index shapes).","files":null}]}